-- Triumph International Plans to Buy Out Shareholders, FTD Reports
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2011-12-22T07:07:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-22/triumph-international-plans-to-buy-out-shareholders-ftd-reports.html
Triumph International AG (TRI)  plans to
buy out the remaining 400 shareholders in the company, which own
4 percent of its stock, the  Financial Times Deutschland  reported
today, without saying where it got the information.  The shareholders will be offered 76.55 euros ($100) a
share, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
